        q: `A 30-year-old sexually active woman presents with vaginal bleeding and discharge. Colposcopic examination reveals an ulcerated lesion arising from the squamocolumnar junction of the uterine cervix. Biopsy results show an invasive tumor containing areas of squamous epithelium in which pearls of keratin can be seen. Molecular analysis reveals the presence of human papillomavirus (HPV) type 16 DNA within the tumor cells. Which of the following molecular abnormalities in this tumor is directly related to infection with HPV-16?`,
