        q: `A 47-year-old man presents with increasing fatigue. The peripheral blood shows a total leukocyte count of 167,500/mL with mature and immature myeloid cells (myelocytes, metamyelocytes, neutrophils) predominating. Cytogenetic analysis of cells obtained from the bone marrow reveal a t(9:22) translocation. Which of the following agents is most likely to be beneficial in the treatment of this condition?`,
