        q: `A 29-year-old woman presents with a 1-month history of a neck mass. On physical examination, a palpable nodule is identified in the right lobe of her thyroid gland. A fine-needle aspirate of the nodule reveals cells consistent with a carcinoma of the thyroid. No other family members are affected by this disorder. Which of the following would you consider to be most relevant in her past history?`,
