        q: `A 64-year-old man has an episode of hemoptysis. A chest radiograph reveals a 5-cm right upper lobe lung mass. A fine-needle aspirate of this mass yields cells consistent with small cell carcinoma. On physical examination, the patient is found to have puffiness of the face, pedal edema, and systolic hypertension. A bone scan shows no metastases. Serum level of which of the following is most likely to be elevated?`,
