        q: `A 66-year-old man with chronic cough and recent hemoptysis has a chest radiograph that shows a 6-cm right lung mass. A sputum cytologic analysis reveals cells consistent with squamous cell carcinoma. Where are metastases from this neoplasm most likely to be found?`,
