        q: `A 33-year-old woman has a routine physical examination. There are no abnormal findings. As part of the pelvic examination, a Pap test is performed. Cytological examination of the cells obtained from the Pap test demonstrates severe epithelial dysplasia. Based on this observation, what would you tell this patient?`,
