        q: `A family history of colon cancer is elicited from a 36-year-old man. Based on this history, a screening colonoscopy is performed, and the cecum and ascending colon are found to contain five polyps, ranging from 0.5 to 2 cm in diameter. They are excised and examined microscopically. The 2-cm polyp contains a focus of adenocarcinoma. Inherited mutations in genes encoding which of the following types of proteins are most likely to be involved in the causation of this tumor?`,
