        q: `A 15-year-old boy presents with swelling of the lower end of the femur close to the knee joint. X-rays show a mass arising from the femur that invades surrounding soft tissue. A biopsy reveals an osteosarcoma. The attending physician tells the family that this tumor is very aggressive and very likely to develop metastases. Which of the following is most likely to be the initial site of metastases?`,
